6
00:00:45,200 --> 00:00:52,000
<i>备注: 本集字幕时间轴根据2013年发布的动画版对齐调整</i>

7
00:01:08,064 --> 00:01:24,224
VARGA: See, it is working. Zondal is coming to life. Zondal. Zondal. Zondal.
看, 起作用了。Zondal就要醒过来了, Zondal, Zondal, Zondal

8
00:01:30,332 --> 00:01:31,343
JAMIE: Wish me luck, Doctor.
祝我好运, 博士

9
00:01:31,434 --> 00:01:37,940
DOCTOR: You take care of yourself, Jamie, and keep an eye on Arden. I don't think he quite realises how dangerous this creature is.
你自己小心, Jamie, 盯着点Arden。我觉得他不清楚这生物有多危险

10
00:01:39,101 --> 00:01:40,689
JAMIE: After what's happened here? He must be blind.
不是刚有人被袭击了吗？他要不知道就太瞎了

11
00:01:40,801 --> 00:01:44,240
DOCTOR: Well, he's a scientist and a bit inclined to have his head in the air. You know what they're like.
哦, 他是个科学家, 有点一头扎在空气中。你知道他们是什么样的

12
00:01:44,340 --> 00:01:45,750
JAMIE: Aye, I certainly do.
是的, 我当然知道

13
00:01:45,880 --> 00:01:47,390
ARDEN: Are you all ready, lad?
你都准备好了吗, 小伙子？

14
00:01:48,550 --> 00:01:49,461
JAMIE: Aye, let's away.
是, 我们走吧

15
00:01:49,490 --> 00:01:50,180
DOCTOR: Good luck.
好运

16
00:01:50,250 --> 00:01:52,781
ARDEN: Now we don't know how many of them there are, so we'll have to tread carefully.
既然我们也不清楚他们到底有多少, 我们必须得小心应对

17
00:01:52,881 --> 00:01:56,159
CLENT: You will not expose yourself to any unnecessary violence, Arden?
不到万不得已不要采取极端手段, 你不会的吧, Arden？

18
00:01:56,208 --> 00:02:00,841
ARDEN: Now listen, Clent, we both know that I'm responsible for what has happened.
现在听着, Clent, 我们都知道对于所发生的事情我是负有责任的。

19
00:02:01,208 --> 00:02:07,841
If I hadn't brought that creature back here in the first place, none of this would have occurred. I also caused the death of Davis. I can't forget that, either.
如果不是我一开始把那个生物带回这里来, 这些事情都不会发生。是我造成了Davis的不幸, 我不会忘记的

20
00:02:08,499 --> 00:02:15,217
CLENT: Well, you just remember your mission, that's all. And no wild sorties after the girl. It's vital that you get your information back to us immediately.
好, 你就记住你的任务就行了。不要被那个女孩儿的事情纠缠住。一有信息就马上返回才是最重要的

21
00:02:15,758 --> 00:02:19,489
JAMIE: Look, we'll not leave Victoria to the warriors, if that's what you mean. If there's half a chance of us two
听着, 我们不会把 Victoria 留给那些勇士。如果你是这个意思, 我们俩半点机会也没有

22
00:02:19,558 --> 00:02:25,099
CLENT: You will take your orders from Scientist Arden! Act according to your priorities, Arden.
你要听从科学家Arden的命令！ 你也得做出带队者的样子, Arden

23
00:02:25,239 --> 00:02:26,089
ARDEN: Come along, boy.
来吧, 孩子

24
00:02:26,179 --> 00:02:26,989
CLENT: Arden?
Arden?

25
00:02:27,089 --> 00:02:27,589
ARDEN: Yes?
怎么?

26
00:02:30,888 --> 00:02:37,825
CLENT: Don't be to too hard on yourself. Scientists must question, you know.
别对自己太苛刻了。科学家负责提出问题的, 你知道的。

27
00:02:37,888 --> 00:02:42,825
I mean, if I'd been in your shoes I think I'd have done the same.
我的意思是, 如果当时是我, 我也会做同样的事情。

28
00:02:42,888 --> 00:02:49,825
I'd have, I'd have brought it back. So, anyway, good luck.
我一样也会把它带回来。所以,不管怎样, 祝你好

29
00:02:50,647 --> 00:02:51,676
DOCTOR: Good luck, Jamie!
好运, Jamie

30
00:02:51,676 --> 00:02:52,267
JAMIE: And you, Doctor.
你也是, 博士

31
00:02:53,836 --> 00:02:57,393
CLENT: Well, Doctor, let's see you go into action. I'll just get Miss Garrett to take you over the set-up here.
对了, 博士, 你也开始动手吧。我会让 Garrett 小姐帮你把这里准备好

32
00:02:58,061 --> 00:03:02,261
DOCTOR: Miss Garrett? Oh, no, no. There's no need to go into formalities.
Garrett小姐？不用, 不用, 不用这么麻烦

33
00:03:02,261 --> 00:03:06,363
CLENT: Miss Garrett? I like things done properly. Where is she?
Garrett小姐呢？我想这件事赶紧完成, 她去哪儿了

34
00:03:06,442 --> 00:03:12,841
DOCTOR: Now Clent, just remember I am not a member of your staff. I'm just a working guest, as you might say.
Clent, 你得记住，我不是你团队中的一员。我只是临时来帮忙的就是了

35
00:03:13,483 --> 00:03:15,673
CLENT: Yes, of course. But this is a formal establishment, and our regulations
是的, 当然。但这里的建设是正式的, 还有章程

36
00:03:15,733 --> 00:03:20,543
DOCTOR: Your regulations do not apply to me. I work in my own way, freely.
你的章程对我不起作用, 我按我自己的方式来做。

37
00:03:22,093 --> 00:03:28,883
CLENT: I see. Like Penley. Regulations seemed to bother him, too. Probably caused his eventual breakdown, in fact.
明白了, 就像Penly一样。这些章程似乎很困扰他, 可能正是这个导致了他最后的崩溃

38
00:03:28,973 --> 00:03:31,353
DOCTOR: Breakdown? I thought you said he defected?
崩溃？我记得你说他开小差了？

39
00:03:32,943 --> 00:03:40,363
CLENT: Did I? Well, one thing lead to another, naturally. He was under a great deal of pressure. Just too much for him, that's all.
是吗？哦, 事情自然是一件接着一件。他当时顶着的压力很大, 对他来说太大了, 就这样

40
00:03:40,494 --> 00:03:41,903
DOCTOR: Oh, I see.
哦, 我明白了

41
00:03:45,064 --> 00:03:47,093
STORR: A creature growing out of the ice! Bah!
冰里面出来一个怪物！切

42
00:03:47,262 --> 00:03:50,864
PENLEY: I assure you that what I saw was very real. And terrifying.
我向你保证我所看见非常真实, 还很吓人

43
00:03:50,904 --> 00:03:57,004
STORR: You've been out on the mountain too long. It takes some people that way. Especially the brainy ones.
你已经在山上呆得太久了, 就会让某些人出现这个, 尤其是用脑较多的人 

44
00:03:57,004 --> 00:04:00,613
PENLEY: Hmmm. Very well, don't believe me, but I still intend to find out.
唔, 好吧, 你不相信我。但我还是打算去搞明白

45
00:04:02,524 --> 00:04:06,844
STORR: Ah well, you can leave me out of your fun and games. I've got enough troubles of my own.
好, 你自己去找你的乐子玩你的游戏吧, 我自己这里已经不少麻烦了

46
00:04:06,844 --> 00:04:11,494
PENLEY: You're fit enough now. To do the cooking, at least. Thanks to science.
你恢复得还可以了, 至少可以做做饭。感谢科学

47
00:04:11,624 --> 00:04:18,554
STORR: Science! Och, it wasn't science, it was just good plain doctoring.
科学, 哦, 可不是科学, 只是一点点简单的医术。

48
00:04:18,624 --> 00:04:24,554
And if you smirk again like that, I'll crack your head open with this.
如果你还要像刚才那样傻笑, 我就那这个把你脑袋拧下来

49
00:04:24,674 --> 00:04:29,236
PENLEY: Yes, you're definitely back to your normal witty self. What's the matter?
是, 但你至少又会开玩笑了是吧。什么情况？

50
00:04:30,225 --> 00:04:31,511
STORR: Someone's outside.
外面有人

51
00:04:32,073 --> 00:04:40,344
PENLEY: They must have tracked me here from the base. Hide yourself. We don't want you carted off to Africa yet. You!
他们肯定从基地跟着我到这里来的, 你藏起来。我们可不想你被运到非洲去

52
00:04:47,678 --> 00:04:50,564
GARRETT: I followed you. It's all right, I'm alone.
我跟踪了你, 不过没关系, 就我一个人

53
00:04:52,827 --> 00:04:53,857
PENLEY: What do you want?
你想要干什么

54
00:04:54,116 --> 00:04:59,247
GARRETT: Elric, we're in desperate trouble at the base. You're the only one who can help us.
Elric, 我们基地陷入了大麻烦。你是唯一能帮助我们的

55
00:04:59,588 --> 00:05:02,858
PENLEY: Clent doesn't need me. All he wants is a mirror. Preferably rose-tinted.
Clent 不需要我。他想要的只是一面镜子。最好还是玫瑰色的

56
00:05:03,277 --> 00:05:06,180
GARRETT: He does need you, to make the ioniser work again.
他需要你, 让离子器能够恢复工作

57
00:05:07,371 --> 00:05:08,340
PENLEY: Is that all?
就这个？

58
00:05:09,739 --> 00:05:13,838
GARRETT: No. He's faced with having to report the full situation to World Control.
不止。他现在必须得向世界总控中心报告总体情况了

59
00:05:14,477 --> 00:05:22,008
PENLEY: Oh well, now we're coming to it, aren't we? The great Clent would have to admit failure. That's it, isn't it?
哈, 那我们得去吧, 是不？伟大的Clent得承认他的失败了, 是吧

60
00:05:22,477 --> 00:05:28,108
Poor old Clent. He never could face the music.
可怜的老Clent，他可能无法面对这个。

61
00:05:28,477 --> 00:05:32,908
Here, what about this creature at the glacier?
对了, 那个冰川怪兽怎么样了

62
00:05:34,199 --> 00:05:38,997
GARRETT: That's only part of our trouble. The real problem is the ioniser. Will you come?
那还只是麻烦的一部分。真正的问题还是离子器。你会来吗？

63
00:05:39,199 --> 00:05:42,051
PENLEY: It's typical of him to send you, instead of armed guards.
还真是他的典型作风，他派你来，而不是派带武器的警卫来

64
00:05:42,109 --> 00:05:45,109
GARRETT: He doesn't know I'm here. I'm asking you.
他不知道我来这里, 是我在问你

65
00:05:46,721 --> 00:05:47,779
PENLEY: I won't come.
我不会去

66
00:05:48,749 --> 00:05:57,109
GARRETT: But you can't just step aside. A man like you, living like a scavenger? It's utterly wrong. Civilisation needs you.
但你不能遛边站啊。一个像你这样的人, 过得像个拾荒者一样。这是全然不对的, 文明世界需要你

67
00:05:57,839 --> 00:06:06,910
PENLEY: Jane, I chose this existence. I chose it because I refuse to be sucked into that computerised ant-heap you call a civilisation.
Jane, 这种情况是我自己选择的。我这么选择就是因为我拒绝那个被电脑占据的世界, 你所谓的文明世界。

68
00:06:07,139 --> 00:06:11,910
I'm a man, not a machine. I will not return.
我是一个人, 不是一台机器。我不会回去的

69
00:06:12,219 --> 00:06:13,719
GARRETT: Not even to save the world?
拯救世界也不管了？

70
00:06:13,819 --> 00:06:22,255
PENLEY: Save the world? Well, that has a fine Clentian ring to it. No thanks, no. It'll take more than me to do that.
拯救世界？呵, 那还真是Clent的做派啊。不,谢谢了。我担当不了这个重任

71
00:06:22,519 --> 00:06:31,255
But don't you worry, you don't get rid of my sort all that easily. Machines corrode and rust, but mankind goes on.
但你不要担心, 你也没法完全甩掉我这类人。机器会锈蚀会坏掉, 但人类还将继续

72
00:06:31,819 --> 00:06:36,255
You'll find Clent one of these days in a museum, like that ancient stove, with an inscription round him.
到了那一天你会在博物馆里面找到Clent的, 就像那些古代的炉子, 周边还刻着铭文

73
00:06:36,819 --> 00:06:43,255
Robotised human mark two, now extinct. But you'll find others like me still alive.
"机器人类第二代, 已灭绝"。不过你会发现我这类人还活着

74
00:06:43,565 --> 00:06:47,786
GARRETT: Surely, Elric, that's all the more reason to come back. To change things.
当然, Elric, 这更加是你要回来的原因, 去改变一些东西

75
00:06:47,786 --> 00:06:54,073
PENLEY: Don't you understand, Jane? Clent's just a talker. He's a glib political animal.
你不明白吗, Jane? Clent 只会侃侃而谈, 他是能说善道的政治动物

76
00:06:54,286 --> 00:07:00,073
Even if I did change things, the Clent's of this world would still come out on top.
就算我改变了一些东西, 但这个世界的Clent还是会跑到顶上去

77
00:07:01,286 --> 00:07:07,073
Running things according to their own whims and indulgences. And the pity of it is, they believe they're right.
凭着一时的喜好, 他们这样, 他们那样。但遗憾的是, 他们还认为他们是对的

78
00:07:08,661 --> 00:07:12,632
GARRETT: Then you leave me no alternative. You will come, and now!
这样我就别无选择了, 你得来, 现在就走

79
00:07:13,413 --> 00:07:20,350
PENLEY: You must be desperate. But tranquillising me isn't going to make it any easier. You'd never be able to carry me all that way.
你肯定都绝望了。但招安了我也不会让事情变得简单。你不可能一直这样抗着我

80
00:07:20,481 --> 00:07:21,352
STORR: Oh no you don't!
哦, 你别这样

81
00:07:21,392 --> 00:07:22,482
GARRETT: Who's this?
这是谁？

82
00:07:22,692 --> 00:07:24,974
PENLEY: Just a friend. Now what are you going to do?
只是一个朋友。你打算干什么？

83
00:07:26,366 --> 00:07:29,577
GARRETT: Return to base and wait for the inevitable disaster.
回到基地, 等着避不可避的灾难来临

84
00:07:29,678 --> 00:07:34,917
STORR: Oh no, you don't. I'm not having you set the dogs on me. I'd as soon put an end to her game. Give me that.
哦, 不要这样。我可受不了这个(?), 我要终结她的这个游戏。把那个给我

85
00:07:34,988 --> 00:07:36,387
PENLEY: Storr, no. She won't put us away.
Storr, 不要。她不会把我们带走的

86
00:07:37,347 --> 00:07:38,507
GARRETT: No, I won't.
不, 我不会

87
00:07:38,727 --> 00:07:40,167
STORR: I don't trust any of them.
他们中的任何一个我都不相信

88
00:07:40,167 --> 00:07:45,756
GARRETT: Please trust me enough to come with me to safety. Apart from the danger of the glacier, these creatures.
请相信我, 跟我去是安全的地方。那些冰川才是危险的, 那些怪物

89
00:07:45,817 --> 00:07:55,902
PENLEY: Oh yes, your ice warriors. Well, we shall just have to take our chance. No, I won't return. And now you must go.
哦, 对, 你的寒冰勇士。我们只能试试自己的运气了。不, 我不会回去的。你现在得走了

90
00:07:56,117 --> 00:08:03,902
But if Sir Genius does have trouble with the ioniser, look up my notes on the Omega factor.
如果天才先生在离子器方面还是碰到困难的话, 翻一翻我的笔记里面关于Omega因子的那部分

91
00:08:05,361 --> 00:08:06,614
GARRETT: Thank you for that at least.
谢谢你告诉我这个

92
00:08:10,652 --> 00:08:12,841
STORR: This ice warrior. It's real then.
这个寒冰勇士, 是真的了？

93
00:08:12,902 --> 00:08:15,682
PENLEY: Oh yes. And I'm going up there again.
是的。我打算再去那里

94
00:08:15,801 --> 00:08:16,871
STORR: But why, man?
为什么？

95
00:08:17,648 --> 00:08:23,218
PENLEY: Because I must know. Now, put this knife to more sensible use.
因为我必须搞明白。现在, 把这把刀用在正事上吧

96
00:08:26,471 --> 00:08:32,374
VARGA: If you value life, obey, and do not anger us.
如果你惜命的话, 就照做, 不要激怒我们

97
00:08:32,654 --> 00:08:35,766
VICTORIA: I want to go back to my friends.
我想回到我的朋友们那里去

98
00:08:35,865 --> 00:08:43,985
VARGA: Perhaps later. For the moment, you are useful to us. Zondal.
也许晚点可以。但现在, 你对我们有用。Zondal

99
00:08:44,020 --> 00:08:45,364
ZONDAL: Commander.
指挥官

100
00:08:46,117 --> 00:08:52,166
VARGA: You will locate our buried spaceship without delay.
你马上定位埋在下面的飞船, 立刻进行

101
00:08:52,316 --> 00:08:55,285
ZONDAL: That will not be difficult.
那应该不难

102
00:08:56,506 --> 00:09:01,006
VARGA: You will excavate sufficient space to form a cave.
你倒腾一点空间出来, 形成一个洞窟

103
00:09:01,136 --> 00:09:03,167
ZONDAL: A cave.
一个洞窟

104
00:09:03,257 --> 00:09:05,007
VARGA: To act as a trap.
可以用作陷阱

105
00:09:05,126 --> 00:09:08,717
VICTORIA: A trap? Who for?
陷阱？做什么用的？

106
00:09:08,807 --> 00:09:14,146
VARGA: Do not interfere. Your friends may attack us.
不要插话。你的朋友可能攻击我们

107
00:09:14,187 --> 00:09:18,028
VICTORIA: But they don't want to attack you. They could help you.
但他们不想要攻击你们, 他们可以帮你们

108
00:09:18,057 --> 00:09:20,247
VARGA: We do not need help.
我们不需要帮助

109
00:09:20,317 --> 00:09:23,406
VICTORIA: You'd still be frozen and dead if it wasn't for us.
如果不是我们的话, 你还在冰冻着

110
00:09:23,466 --> 00:09:25,878
VARGA: You are a child.
你是个孩子

111
00:09:25,958 --> 00:09:27,419
VICTORIA: Oh, why won't you listen?
哦, 你为什么不听

112
00:09:32,734 --> 00:09:33,826
VARGA: Commence.
动手

113
00:09:34,944 --> 00:09:37,105
VICTORIA: What are you going to do with me?
你们打算拿我怎么样？

114
00:09:39,683 --> 00:09:44,145
VARGA: Bait. Bait for the trap.
诱饵, 做陷阱的诱饵

115
00:09:47,655 --> 00:10:59,617
ZONDAL: Activate direction sensors. Steady.
激活方向传感器。稳定。sync

116
00:09:59,955 --> 00:10:18,617
Sonic stalls ready. Set to wide impact. Take aim. Continuous fire!
split声波设备就绪。设定为大面积。瞄准, 持续喷射！

117
00:10:29,280 --> 00:10:48,861
DOCTOR: If I was to reverse the sequence to give a density ratio. Where did I? Yes, here we are.
如果我反转这个过程, 加大密度。我刚才到哪儿了？对了,到这里了

118
00:10:49,280 --> 00:11:01,861
If I reverse the sequence to give a density ratio. Excuse me. Excuse me! Yes.
如果我反转这个过程, 加大密度。让让，让让, 好了

119
00:11:02,832 --> 00:11:08,891
CLENT: Genius at work, I see. Good morning Doctor.
工作起来就灵感爆发啊, 早上好博士

120
00:11:08,951 --> 00:11:11,451
DOCTOR: Mmm? Yes.
呒, 是

121
00:11:13,051 --> 00:11:16,511
CLENT: Well, this is all very impressive, Doctor, but don't you think it'd be simpler to use a computer?
这都很让人折服, 博士。但你不觉得用电脑会简单得多吗？

122
00:11:16,622 --> 00:11:18,330
DOCTOR: Four. What computer?
四。什么电脑?

123
00:11:18,400 --> 00:11:19,621
CLENT: The base computer.
基地的电脑

124
00:11:19,692 --> 00:11:26,912
DOCTOR: Six. Yes, they're useful for digital analysis, but I very rarely use them, except when I have to.
六。是的, 用它们做做数学分析还是很有用的, 但我很少用它们, 除非万不得已。

125
00:11:27,192 --> 00:11:31,912
There is one thing you could do for me which would be very important.
但有一件事你得帮我一下, 非常重要

126
00:11:32,031 --> 00:11:33,192
CLENT: Yes, yes, anything. What is it?
好的, 好的, 任何事情都行。具体是。。。?

127
00:11:33,292 --> 00:11:39,532
DOCTOR: Lend me a pencil. Oh, that would be even better.
借我一只铅笔。哦, 这就更好了

128
00:11:40,622 --> 00:11:43,682
CLENT: Doctor, would you mind explaining just what it is that you are
博士, 你是否介意介绍一下刚才你是在。。。？

129
00:11:43,752 --> 00:11:47,133
DOCTOR: Now, this is wrong, this is wrong. It's not right. There's something missing.
现在, 这样不对, 这样不对。漏了什么东西

130
00:11:48,632 --> 00:11:49,604
CLENT: Would these figures help?
这些数据有帮助吗？

131
00:11:49,693 --> 00:11:50,782
DOCTOR: Supposing I? What are they?
跟我说吗？这是什么？

132
00:11:50,822 --> 00:11:52,163
CLENT: Data readings from the other bases.
其它基地传过来的数据

133
00:11:52,223 --> 00:11:53,413
DOCTOR: Oh, computer checked, I hope?
哦, 电脑已经检查过了吧, 我想？

134
00:11:53,413 --> 00:11:54,383
CLENT: Of course.
当然

135
00:11:54,383 --> 00:11:55,634
DOCTOR: Oh, thank heavens for that.
哦, 感谢上天

136
00:11:55,634 --> 00:11:57,032
GARRETT: Doctor, I've found something here that I think you might
博士, 我想我发现了点东西, 你可能会。。。

137
00:11:57,032 --> 00:12:00,447
CLENT: Where have you been, Miss Garrett? Your instructions were to help the Doctor, were they not?
你去哪里了, Garrett 小姐？给你的指令是帮助博士, 不是吗？

138
00:12:00,518 --> 00:12:07,379
GARRETT: Yes, Leader Clent. I have been looking up Scientist Penley's notes. These. Could these help?
是的, Clent 队长。我在查阅科学家Penley的笔记。这些有帮助吗？

139
00:12:07,470 --> 00:12:16,442
DOCTOR: What are they? Omega. Well, what does he mean? Omega. What does he?
这是什么？Omega。他这是什么意思？Omega, 他这是。。。

140
00:12:17,470 --> 00:12:25,442
Wait a minute. Wait a minute! Yes! Yes, of course.
等一下, 等一下。对了！对了, 当然是这样

141
00:12:25,470 --> 00:12:37,442
The Omega Factor! There and here and there.
Omega 因子, 这里, 这里, 还有这里

142
00:12:37,470 --> 00:12:40,442
Yes! Ha ha! Your friend Penley is very clever.
对了, 哈哈, 你这个朋友Penley 还真是聪明

143
00:12:40,512 --> 00:12:41,573
CLENT: Is that it?
就这样？

144
00:12:41,633 --> 00:12:42,633
DOCTOR: Yes, that's it!
对, 就这样

145
00:12:42,702 --> 00:12:43,834
CLENT: That's fantastic.
那太棒了

146
00:12:43,923 --> 00:12:46,333
DOCTOR: Oh, when you've been at it as long as I have it's nothing.
哦，如果你在这上面花我这么多时间，就不是问题了

147
00:12:46,402 --> 00:12:48,723
GARRETT: Do you think it could possibly work?
你觉得这能行吗？

148
00:12:48,754 --> 00:12:49,742
CLENT: It's very possible.
很有可能

149
00:12:49,787 --> 00:12:52,123
DOCTOR: Possible? It's perfect! Well, it's nearly perfect.
只是可能？是完美！嗯, 基本完美

150
00:12:53,143 --> 00:12:53,928
CLENT: We shall see.
我们再看看

151
00:12:54,018 --> 00:12:55,177
DOCTOR: Oh, it'll work, all right.
哦, 它能行的, 没事

152
00:12:55,221 --> 00:12:57,027
CLENT: The computer will confirm that, I'm sure.
电脑会证实这个的, 我肯定

153
00:12:57,717 --> 00:12:58,528
DOCTOR: Computer?
电脑

154
00:12:58,628 --> 00:12:59,997
GARRETT: Well, everything's checked.
是啊, 每件事都得检查一下

155
00:13:01,406 --> 00:13:02,322
DOCTOR: I resent that!
我讨厌这个

156
00:13:02,641 --> 00:13:04,261
CLENT: Just normal practice, Doctor.
只是惯例而已, 博士

157
00:13:04,261 --> 00:13:05,981
DOCTOR: It should be the other way round.
应该反过来才对

158
00:13:06,042 --> 00:13:11,856
CLENT: We have to be quite sure. It'll only take a matter of seconds.
我们必须得确保这个, 就几秒钟的事情

159
00:13:12,042 --> 00:13:18,856
Copy all this down, Miss Garrett, and then we can feed it through the computer and do a simulator run. I'll just go and set it up.
把这些都抄下来, Garrett小姐。我们把它送入电脑里面去, 做一次模拟运行。我这就去把它准备好

160
00:13:19,447 --> 00:13:20,986
DOCTOR: I shall demand an apology, you know.
我真需要一个道歉，是不

161
00:13:22,501 --> 00:13:23,561
GARRETT: We may not have time for that.
我们可能没有这个时间

162
00:13:23,591 --> 00:13:26,400
DOCTOR: Well, I'm glad you had time to look up Penley's notes.
哈, 我很高兴你有时间去看Penley 的笔记

163
00:13:27,121 --> 00:13:28,271
GARRETT: I thought it might be useful.
我只是想到可能会有帮助

164
00:13:29,368 --> 00:13:31,413
DOCTOR: Pity that he turned traitor.
很可惜他成了叛徒

165
00:13:32,073 --> 00:13:37,894
GARRETT: Oh, Clent might call him that, but he's still the most brilliant scientist we have.
哦, Clent 才这么说他。但他仍然是我们这里最耀眼的科学家

166
00:13:38,024 --> 00:13:40,723
DOCTOR: Oh? Oh, it's nice to see he still has some friends in the base.
哦, 很高兴看到他在基地里还有一些朋友

167
00:13:41,774 --> 00:13:50,597
ARDEN: Glacier task unit. Leader Clent, please. Leader Clent, please.
这里是冰川任务组。呼叫组长Clent, 请回话。呼叫组长Clent, 请回话

168
00:13:52,068 --> 00:13:53,526
CLENT: Clent here. Report.
我是Clent, 请讲

169
00:13:55,107 --> 00:13:56,647
ARDEN: We've arrived at the glacier site. There's something strange.
我们已经到达冰川, 这里有些奇怪的情况

170
00:13:57,767 --> 00:13:58,476
CLENT: What is?
是什么

171
00:13:58,607 --> 00:14:02,986
ARDEN: The ice face. It's been excavated into a cave.
冰的表层, 被挖开了一个冰窟

172
00:14:03,107 --> 00:14:04,007
DOCTOR: How?
怎么弄的？

173
00:14:04,076 --> 00:14:05,946
ARDEN: By some kind of tool, I think.
某种工具吧, 我觉得

174
00:14:05,977 --> 00:14:07,777
CLENT: Is there any sign of a spacecraft?
有没有飞船的迹象

175
00:14:07,876 --> 00:14:08,937
ARDEN: Yes.
有

176
00:14:08,967 --> 00:14:10,296
DOCTOR: There is? Where?
这里吗？什么地方？

177
00:14:10,356 --> 00:14:14,718
ARDEN: Well, at the back of the cave, there's what looks like a metal door in the ice.
哦, 就在洞窟的后面, 冰里面看起来像是有一道金属门

178
00:14:18,780 --> 00:14:20,491
ARDEN: The place is apparently deserted.
这个地方看起来已经废弃了

179
00:14:21,801 --> 00:14:23,421
DOCTOR: Well make sure you don't go too near.
小心不要太靠近了

180
00:14:25,540 --> 00:14:28,970
CLENT: Excuse me. Take the necessary readings, and leave quickly, Arden.
打断一下, 记录下数据就感觉离开, Arden

181
00:14:29,132 --> 00:14:30,351
ARDEN: I'll take care.
我会关注的

182
00:14:32,326 --> 00:14:33,475
JAMIE: What readings?
什么数据？

183
00:14:33,566 --> 00:14:36,415
ARDEN: Radiation, magnetic field and ion density. Won't take long.
辐射、磁场、离子浓度, 不会花太久的

184
00:14:37,836 --> 00:14:39,267
JAMIE: I don't fancy this place.
我不喜欢这个地方

185
00:14:40,177 --> 00:14:45,326
ARDEN: There's never been such a discovery as this. All my life
从来没有过这样的发现, 我这一辈子

186
00:14:54,137 --> 00:15:04,586
VICTORIA: No! Oh Jamie, no! What have you done to him? You killed them!
不。Jamie, 不！你把他怎么了？ 你杀了他们！

187
00:15:04,866 --> 00:15:07,575
VARGA: It was necessary.
这是必要的

188
00:15:07,676 --> 00:15:09,926
VICTORIA: Oh, you're monsters!
你们这些怪物

189
00:15:10,296 --> 00:15:12,005
VARGA: Remove her inside.
把她弄到里面去

190
00:15:12,037 --> 00:15:24,110
VICTORIA: Oh, leave me alone! Oh, please. Haven't you done enough? Please, leave me alone! I want to go back! Please!
哦, 放开我, 哦, 不要。你们还没满意吗？求你们了, 放开我！我要回去

191
00:15:31,691 --> 00:15:34,241
ZONDAL: There may be more of them.
他们还有很多人

192
00:15:35,463 --> 00:15:40,266
VARGA: If more of them come, we will destroy them.
如果他们再来人, 我们把他们都干掉。

193
00:15:40,463 --> 00:15:48,266
If no more of them come, we will know there are not enough of them to resist us.
如果他们不再来人, 我们也就能知道他们没有多少人，不足以抵抗我们

194
00:15:48,594 --> 00:15:51,323
ZONDAL: Let us destroy the girl now.
我们现在干掉这个女孩儿吧

195
00:15:53,332 --> 00:15:59,190
VARGA: They came after her. She is obviously of some value to them.
他们是为她而来的, 所以看来她对他们有某种价值

196
00:15:59,338 --> 00:16:01,848
ZONDAL: Then they will try again.
所以他们还是再次尝试

197
00:16:03,662 --> 00:16:13,169
VARGA: We shall be ready for them. But first, Zondal, you have a task to complete.
我们要做好准备应对。但Zondal, 首先你有一个任务要完成

198
00:16:13,662 --> 00:16:24,169
The propulsion unit. It must be made to function. Time is vital. You must succeed.
那个推进器, 必须要可以工作。时间很紧, 你必须成功

199
00:16:24,228 --> 00:16:25,971
ZONDAL: Yes, Commander.
是, 指挥官

200
00:16:26,951 --> 00:16:27,982
VARGA: Come.
来吧

201
00:16:58,785 --> 00:17:01,535
CLENT: We've just finished programming the computer. We shall have the result very quickly.
我们已经完成电脑编码了, 很快就可以得到结果

202
00:17:01,725 --> 00:17:04,096
DOCTOR: Isn't it about time that Arden and Jamie reported again?
是不是到了Arden 和Jamie 再次报告的时间了？

203
00:17:06,954 --> 00:17:11,154
CLENT: Yes, that's true. But you know what Arden is, with his scientific curiosity.
是, 还真是。但你也知道Arden 是什么样的, 科学好奇心一上来。。。

204
00:17:11,184 --> 00:17:12,873
DOCTOR: Yes, very human. I'm worried about them too.
是的, 很人性。我担心他们

205
00:17:12,873 --> 00:17:21,743
CLENT: Yes, I'll do it if you don't mind. Leader Clent calling Scientist Arden. Arden? Do you receive me?
是的, 你不介意的话我来吧。组长Clent 呼叫科学家Arden。Arden, 你能收到吗？

206
00:17:23,753 --> 00:17:27,245
DOCTOR: He's not answering. Perhaps something has happened to them.
他没回答, 可能发生了什么情况

207
00:17:27,304 --> 00:17:32,714
CLENT: It looks as if he's. Arden. For heaven's sake man, come in!
看起来是。Arden, 老天啊, 快回答

208
00:17:34,254 --> 00:17:49,493
DOCTOR: Jamie, answer me! Jamie, what's happened? Jamie! Jamie!
Jamie, 回答我！Jamie, 发生什么事了? Jamie, Jamie!

209
00:18:11,976 --> 00:18:14,628
DOCTOR: I will never forgive myself if anything's happened to Jamie.
如果Jamie 出了什么事, 我不会原谅自己的

210
00:18:14,937 --> 00:18:16,625
CLENT: What about this project with Arden missing?
如果Arden 失踪了, 这个项目可怎么办？

211
00:18:16,655 --> 00:18:18,667
DOCTOR: Oh, your ioniser will work all right.
哦, 你的离子器会工作得很好的

212
00:18:18,816 --> 00:18:23,579
CLENT: I hope so. I'm not sure that I trust your judgement yet, Doctor.
期望如此。我不确定是否能完全相信你的判断, 博士

213
00:18:23,668 --> 00:18:26,016
DOCTOR: What do you mean, I'm only human? Well as a matter of fact
你什么意思？我只是人类而已？事实上。。。

214
00:18:26,016 --> 00:18:26,505
GARRETT: It works!
可以了

215
00:18:26,555 --> 00:18:26,947
DOCTOR: I told you it would.
我告诉过你它会的

216
00:18:26,947 --> 00:18:27,346
GARRETT: The equation works!
这个方程式有效！

217
00:18:27,719 --> 00:18:28,491
DOCTOR: I told you it would.
我告诉过你它会的

218
00:18:29,894 --> 00:18:40,879
CLENT: Good. Good. Jolly good. Success is at last possible. Inform all ioniser bases, Miss Garrett. Thank you, Doctor. It's a triumph.
好, 好, 很好。至少有成功的可能了。通知所有离子器基地, Garrett 小姐。谢谢你, 博士, 这真是个喜讯

219
00:18:40,989 --> 00:18:47,221
DOCTOR: Very likely. But somewhere, out on that ice face, are two young people for whom I have considerable affection. That is no triumph!
很可能。但我关心的两个年轻人, 还在冰面上某个地方, 这可不是喜讯

220
00:18:47,261 --> 00:18:50,561
CLENT: I appreciate your feelings. I, too, have lost a colleague.
我明白你的感受。我也失去了一位同僚

221
00:18:50,632 --> 00:18:52,029
DOCTOR: They're not colleagues, they're friends.
他们不是同僚, 他们是我的朋友

222
00:18:52,130 --> 00:18:57,939
CLENT: We cannot be sentimental in this situation, Doctor. Our mission continues. We must all play our part.
在这种情况下我们不能感情用事, 博士。我们的任务还得继续, 我们都得做好自己的事情

223
00:18:58,010 --> 00:18:59,362
DOCTOR: I've played mine. It's finished.
我已经做好了我的, 已经完成了

224
00:18:59,460 --> 00:19:12,124
CLENT: What a triumph. Europe saved. Science the victor over nature, and it happened in my sector. Well, it's not the first time.
真是个喜讯啊, 欧洲得救了。科学战胜了自然, 这发生在我的辖区。哈, 这还不是第一次

225
00:19:12,235 --> 00:19:15,191
GARRETT: Now we can go ahead. It only needs programming.
现在我们可以继续了, 只需要一些编程

226
00:19:15,370 --> 00:19:16,662
DOCTOR: Aren't you forgetting something?
你们是不是忘记了一点事情

227
00:19:16,721 --> 00:19:18,520
CLENT: I'm sorry, but some lives are bound to be lost.
抱歉, 但我们不得不付出一些牺牲

228
00:19:18,591 --> 00:19:24,292
DOCTOR: No, no, I don't mean that. Arden. He's not yet completed his mission.
不, 不, 我不是指这个。Arden, 他还没有完成他的任务

229
00:19:24,751 --> 00:19:30,461
GARRETT: Oh yes, of course. The spaceship reactor. We daren't proceed until we've heard from Arden.
哦, 是的, 当然。那个飞船的反应堆。我们接收到Arden 的信息之前是不能贸然继续的

230
00:19:33,717 --> 00:19:35,298
CLENT: Where is he? Where is he? Where is he?
他在哪里？他在哪里？他在哪里？

231
00:19:43,407 --> 00:19:46,587
STORR: What did you have to bring him back here for? Another mouth to feed.
你为什么还得把他带回来？又多了一张嘴吃饭

232
00:19:46,647 --> 00:19:49,996
PENLEY: You may hate scientists, Storr, but there's no need to hate all human beings.
你可以恨科学家, Storr。但没必要恨多有的人

233
00:19:50,057 --> 00:19:52,615
STORR: I don't trust anyone from Clent's base.
我信不过来自Clent 基地的任何一个

234
00:19:52,675 --> 00:19:56,515
JAMIE: Who are you? Where's Arden? What happened?! Oh, my head.
你是谁？Arden 在哪儿？发生了什么？哦, 我的头

235
00:19:56,546 --> 00:19:59,666
PENLEY: Now you must rest. You're suffering from severe shock. Now just lie still.
现在你必须休息, 你经受了严重的惊吓。现在好好躺着

236
00:19:59,769 --> 00:20:01,787
JAMIE: Well, where am I?
那, 我在哪里？

237
00:20:01,887 --> 00:20:04,037
STORR: Ah, never you mind. Somewhere safe.
啊, 别担心这个。一个安全的地方

238
00:20:04,127 --> 00:20:06,107
JAMIE: Well, what happened to me and Arden?
刚才我和Arden 怎么了？

239
00:20:06,137 --> 00:20:09,736
PENLEY: Arden's dead. You were both shot down by the warriors.
Arden 他死了, 你们被寒冰勇士击中了

240
00:20:09,797 --> 00:20:11,217
JAMIE: Arden dead?
Arden 死了？

241
00:20:11,245 --> 00:20:13,247
PENLEY: They used some sort of ray gun.
他们用了某种射线枪

242
00:20:13,308 --> 00:20:15,187
JAMIE: So we failed.
这么说我们失败了

243
00:20:15,246 --> 00:20:18,600
STORR: You came to rescue the girl? Is that it?
你们是来营救那个女孩儿的？是吗？

244
00:20:18,940 --> 00:20:20,338
JAMIE: You've seen Victoria? Is she still alive?
你看见Victoria 了？她还或者吗？

245
00:20:20,384 --> 00:20:21,378
PENLEY: Yes, she is alive.
是的, 他还活着

246
00:20:21,408 --> 00:20:22,908
JAMIE: Then we can still save her! You will help me, please!
那我们还可以救她！你得帮我, 请你帮我！

247
00:20:22,908 --> 00:20:25,169
PENLEY: Now you're not yet well enough. We'll discuss it later.
但你现在的情况还不够好, 我们晚点再讨论这个

248
00:20:25,198 --> 00:20:35,791
JAMIE: No, it'll be to late then. They might. Oh, my head. No, you must help me save Victoria. It'll be too late.
不, 要不然就太迟了。他们可能。。。奥,我的头。你必须帮我救Victoria , 要不然来不及了

249
00:21:06,607 --> 00:21:22,578
VICTORIA: Doctor, if only I could make this thing work. This is Victoria calling the Doctor or Leader Clent. This is Victoria. Please answer me.
博士, 如果我能让这个东西能用就好了。这里是Victoria, 呼叫博士或者组长Clent。我是Victoria, 请回答

250
00:21:27,821 --> 00:21:32,072
ZONDAL: The girl, Commander. She will betray us.
那个女孩儿, 她会背叛我们的。指挥官

251
00:21:33,040 --> 00:21:43,822
VARGA: She has courage. But she is also very stupid to think that we would not watch her every move.
她倒是有勇气。但她也很愚蠢, 以为我们不会盯着她

252
00:21:43,921 --> 00:21:46,533
ZONDAL: She must be stopped.
必须得阻止她

253
00:22:05,826 --> 00:22:08,625
DOCTOR: It's Victoria! Victoria, where are you?
是Victoria. 你在哪儿, Victoria?

254
00:22:09,066 --> 00:22:09,725
VICTORIA: I...
我

255
00:22:09,815 --> 00:22:11,217
VICTORIA: I don't know.
我不知道

256
00:22:11,577 --> 00:22:13,006
VICTORIA: Some sort of cave.
某个洞穴一样的东西

257
00:22:13,066 --> 00:22:14,186
DOCTOR: Are you all right?
你还好吗？

258
00:22:14,286 --> 00:22:19,235
VICTORIA: Yes, but, oh Doctor, something terrible's happened!
是的, 博士。但是, 有可怕的事情要发生了

259
00:22:19,307 --> 00:22:20,085
DOCTOR: What?
什么

260
00:22:20,116 --> 00:22:22,446
VICTORIA: They, they've shot Jamie and Arden!
他们, 他们朝Jamie 和 Arden 开枪了

261
00:22:23,728 --> 00:22:29,348
DOCTOR: What? Well, is he dead? Is, is he wounded? Is he badly wounded?
啊？那, 他死了吗？还是受伤了？伤得严重吗？

262
00:22:29,428 --> 00:22:32,618
VICTORIA: I don't know.
